<task id="configure-mysql-datasource">
  <title>How to Configure MySQL Data Source Drivers</title>
  <taskbody>
    <context>
      <p>To connect to a MySQL server, you need to create a generic JDBC type data source based on
          <xref href="http://www.mysql.com/downloads/connector/j/" format="html" scope="external"
          >the MySQL JDBC driver available on the MySQL website</xref>.</p>
      <p>To configure this data source, follow these steps:</p>
    </context>
    <steps>
      <step>
        <cmd>Go to <xref href="https://www.oxygenxml.com/database_drivers.html" format="html"
            scope="external"/> and download the appropriate MySQL driver.</cmd>
      </step>
      <step>
        <cmd><ph conkeyref="reusables-working-with-databases/open-ds"/></cmd>
      </step>
      <step>
        <cmd><ph conkeyref="reusables-working-with-databases/click-new"/></cmd>
        <stepresult>
          <p>The dialog box for configuring a data source is opened.</p>
          <p>
            <fig product="editor author developer">
              <title>Data Source Drivers Configuration Dialog Box</title>
              <image href="../img/sa_datasource_mysql.png"/>
            </fig>
          </p>
          <p>
            <fig product="editorEclipse authorEclipse developerEclipse">
              <title>Data Source Drivers Configuration Dialog Box</title>
              <image href="../img/ec_datasource_mysql.png"/>
            </fig>
          </p>
        </stepresult>
      </step>
      <step>
        <cmd><ph conkeyref="reusables-working-with-databases/unique-name"/></cmd>
      </step>
      <step>
        <cmd>Select <i>Generic JDBC</i> in the driver <uicontrol>Type</uicontrol> drop-down
          list.</cmd>
      </step>
      <step>
        <cmd>Click the <uicontrol>Add Files</uicontrol> button and select the MySQL driver file that
          you downloaded.</cmd>
        <info>The driver file for the MySQL server is called
          <filepath>mysql-com.jar</filepath>.</info>
      </step>
      <step>
        <cmd><ph conkeyref="reusables-working-with-databases/select-driver-class"/></cmd>
      </step>
      <step>
        <cmd><ph conkeyref="reusables-working-with-databases/step6"/></cmd>
      </step>
      <step>
        <cmd>Continue on to <xref href="configure-mysql-connection.dita#configure-mysql-connection"
            >configure your MySQL connection</xref>.</cmd>
      </step>
    </steps>
  </taskbody>
</task>